
Overview of noun suspicion

The noun suspicion has 4 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (11) intuition, hunch, suspicion -- (an impression that something might be the case; "he had an intuition that something had gone wrong")
2. (2) misgiving, mistrust, distrust, suspicion -- (doubt about someone's honesty)
3. suspicion -- (the state of being suspected; "he tried to shield me from suspicion")
4. suspicion, suspiciousness -- (being of a suspicious nature; "his suspiciousness destroyed his marriage")
